ðŸš© Flag 13 â€“ Approved/Final Bonus Artifact Access

### ðŸŽ¯ Objective
Confirm access to a finalized year-end bonus artifact with sensitive-read classification.

### ðŸ§¾ Summary
This step validates unauthorized access to the **final approved** year-end bonus artifact by hunting for **SensitiveFileRead** events on **sys1-dept** and capturing the exact timestamp tied to the sensitive read activity. Access to the approved bonus file is important because it confirms the attacker reached the finalized, highest-sensitivity payout data and could use it for theft or fraud.

âœ… Finding  
A sensitive-read event was recorded for the finalized file **BonusMatrix_Q4_Approved.xlsx** on **sys1-dept**, indicating unauthorized access under a remote session context.

Solution (requested value): Timestamp of unauthorized sensitive file access:  
**2025-12-03T07:25:39.1653621Z**

### ðŸ”Ž What to Hunt
Events indicating sensitive reads tied to the remote session context responsible for the approved file access.  
Hint: Final version of the file.

### â— Why it matters
This represents direct exposure of the â€œfinal approvedâ€ bonus dataset, confirming the attacker successfully accessed the most valuable compensation artifact.

### ðŸ” KQL Query Used
```kql
DeviceEvents
| where TimeGenerated >= datetime(2025-12-01)
| where DeviceName == "sys1-dept"
| where ActionType == "SensitiveFileRead"
| where FileName has "BonusMatrix_Q4_Approved.xlsx" or FolderPath has "BonusMatrix_Q4_Approved.xlsx"
| project TimeGenerated, DeviceName, ActionType, FileName, FolderPath,
          InitiatingProcessAccountName, InitiatingProcessFileName, InitiatingProcessCommandLine,
          InitiatingProcessRemoteSessionDeviceName, InitiatingProcessRemoteSessionIP
| order by TimeGenerated asc
